&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse - Frome Community Hospital , Marshfield Ward &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse looking for a fresh, new challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a vacancy for a part time registered nurse, 30 hours per week, working within the multi-disciplinary team on Marshfield Ward, Frome Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Frome is in the heart of the beautiful Somerset countryside. The ward has a mix of single and double rooms, all with en-suite facilities as well as communal areas for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff are provided with excellent changing facilities and a staff room with access to outside seating located on the balcony.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will be responsible for all aspects of patient care, from admission through to discharge, using a computerised record keeping system. You will have the opportunity to attend family meetings, undertake ward rounds and be involved in multi-disciplinary team meetings. These all contribute to the decision making process, goal setting and care planning that facilitates a safe discharge home from Hospital. You will provide general nursing care to all of your patients, ensuring they are treated with dignity and respect. You will be able to promote a safe environment within the unit and act as a shift coordinator as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a Registered Nurse who is able to communicate at all levels, have high clinical standards and have the ability to work as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be required to work flexibly on an internal shift rotation, working both days and nights over a seven day period, including bank holidays. In return you will receive enhanced payments for working unsocial hours, a generous holiday entitlement and pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preceptorship nurses are also encouraged to apply, and a full preceptorship programme is offered by the Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicola Murphy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron&lt;/p&gt;
